n-alayhi","tag-authority-al-sultan","tag-bloodshed-safk-al-dima","tag-death-mawt","tag-defense-al-difaa","tag-good-deeds-hasanat","tag-imam-ahmad-ibn-hanbal","tag-intention-al-niyyah","tag-legal-punishment-al-hudud","tag-manners-adab","tag-martyrs-shuhada","tag-rulers","tag-virtue-al-fadail","tag-wealth-al-mal"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-3ER","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":3181,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/05\/13\/defending-life-family-shahid\/","url_meta":{"origin":14065,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Shahid: Killed defending his life is a martyr","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 13, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019id ibn Zayd reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever is killed protecting his property is a martyr. Whoever is killed protecting his religion is a martyr. Whoever is killed protecting his life is a martyr. Whoever is killed protecting his family is a martyr.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25464,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/29\/raising-hands-in-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":14065,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Description of raising the hands in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 29, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would raise his hands parallel to his shoulders when he entered into prayer, and when he exalted Allah for bowing. When he raised his head from bowing, he would likewise raise his hands and say, \u201cAllah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28698,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/05\/children-fasting-ramadan\/","url_meta":{"origin":14065,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Ramadan: Children fasting Ramadan if they are able","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Rabia\u2019 bint Mu\u2019awwidh reported: We would order our children to fast and we would make toys for them out of wool. If one of them cried for food, we would give them those toys until it was time to break fast. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1859, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1136 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":12088,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/02\/06\/eating-dinner-maghrib-prayer\/","url_meta":{"origin":14065,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: Eating dinner before Maghrib prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 6, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf dinner is presented close to the time of prayer, begin eating before you perform sunset prayer and do not need to rush away from your dinner.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 640, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 558 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25503,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/bismillah-begin-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":14065,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Bismillah: Reciting name of Allah to begin prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar, may Allah be pleased with them, would open the prayer by reciting, \u201cAll praise is due to Allah.\u201d (1:1) In the narration of Muslim, Anas said: I did not hear any of them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7633,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/04\/husband-wife-rights-wealth\/","url_meta":{"origin":14065,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Rights: If a husband fails to fulfill his family&#8217;s rights","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 4, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: Hind bint 'Utba came and she said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, Abu Sufyan is a stingy man. Is there any blame on me for using his wealth to feed our dependents?\" The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThere is no blame if you feed them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":